\par
She glanced up at him, then began to walk out again. "Why would you think so?"\par
\par
"Because in the time I've spent with you I've listened to you, and learned."\par
\par
"Why are you spending time with me, Aidan?"\par
\par
"I like you."\par
\par
She shook her head again. "You don't know me. If I haven't figured myself out yet, you can't know me."\par
\par
"I like what I see."\par
\par
"So it's a physical sort of attraction." That quick brow quirked again. "And is that a problem for you, then?"\par
\par
