He frowned as he stepped toward her. "Why would it sound stupid if it's what you're thinking?"\par
\par
"Because I have a habit of saying stupid things when I'm nervous."\par
\par
He slipped the flower stem deeper into her hair as the wind wanted to tug it free again. "I thought you sang when you were nervous."\par
\par
"One or the other," she muttered, moving backward to keep what she thought was a safe distance.\par
\par
"You're nervous now?"\par
\par
"Yes! God!" Knowing she was close to stuttering, she held her hands up to hold him off. "Just stop. I've never had anything tie me up like this. Instant attraction. I said I believe in it, and I do, but I've never felt it before. I have to think about it."\par
\par
