\par
His eyes were so blue, as vivid as the water that stretched to the horizon. It seemed her world turned that single, marvelous color. Her heart began to pound, her vision to blur as it had that first time at Maude's grave.\par
\par
She said his name, just one sigh, then threw her arms around him.\par
\par
